<HEADLINE>
FT  18 AUG 93 / Berkshire Council chief to quit
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MR Tony Allen is resigning as chief executive of Berkshire County Council at
the end of November.
The council, which during his tenure has pioneered contracting-out of
services to the private sector, now intends to devolve power further. It
plans to allow more autonomy to the people who chair committees and to
replace the office of chief executive, with a 'corporate manager'. The
council, jointly controlled by Labour and the Liberal Democrats, said this
was 'one of the most radical reorganisations in local government'.
Mr Allen is believed to disagree with some of the plans.
</TEXT>
