FT  17 AUG 93 / Indonesia eases visa curbs
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   JAKARTA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Seeking to attract more tourists, Indonesia yesterday began allowing
visitors from 45 countries to stay two months without visas, the immigration
office announced, AP reports from Jakarta.
The visa-free visits cannot be extended or used for business purposes.
In 1992, more than 3m foreigners visited Indonesia, up from 2.5m in 1991.
Tourist earnings rose from Dollars 1.4bn in 1989 to Dollars 3.3bn in 1992.
