<HEADLINE>
FT  17 AUG 93 / World Stock Markets: Brazil
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Positive reaction to changes in Brazil's Central Bank command and strong
selective buying due to today's options settlement boosted shares by 6.2 per
cent in heavy trade on the Sao Paulo exchange.
The Bovespa index ended at 77,278, up 4,538 from Friday's close. Volume hit
a record of Cr46.3bn. The options settlements accounted for 50.3 per cent of
the total turnover.
