who tried to sell a 22 per cent stake to Mr Rupert Murdoch in July, only to
be thwarted by Hong Kong's television ownership restrictions.
TVB faces competition with the launch of cable television in Hong Kong on
October 31, and from Mr Murdoch, who recently bought 64 per cent of Star,
the satellite broadcaster.
The interim dividend is 15 cents a share.
