<HEADLINE>
FT  17 AUG 93 / International Company News: Ralston Purina
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIt
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Ralston Purina, the St Louis-based manufacturer of pet food, batteries and a
variety of food products, announced late yesterday that it was considering
spining off its cereal, baby foods and other smaller 'grocery human foods'
businesses as a separately-quoted company, writes Nikki Tait.
Ralston said that the potential demerger would be reviewed by directors at a
board meeting to be held on September 23.
Ralston is a sizeable force in the cereal market, where it is best-known for
the 'Chex' brands, although it ranks behind industry heavyweights, such as
Kellogg and General Mills.
The St Louis group has also been heavily involved in the private label
cereal business, a growing segment of the overall market, and is reckoned to
be the dominant producer.
Its baby-food products are marketed under the 'Beech-Nut' brand name. This
industry has been highly competitive recently, and subject to a price war
between rival manufacturers.
</TEXT>
