<HEADLINE>
FT  17 AUG 93 / International Company News: Textron to sell stake in
insurance unit
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
TEXTRON, the US aerospace group that diversified into financial services
during the 1980s, said yesterday that it planned to sell a minority stake in
its Paul Revere insurance subsidiary, writes Richard Waters in New York.
The intended sale of 17 per cent of the disability insurer signals a plan to
reduce the group's involvement in the financial services business and focus
instead on its manufacturing operations, Textron said. However, it added
that it had 'no present plans' to sell further shares in Paul Revere or any
other financial services business.
Paul Revere, a leading name in the North American individual disability
insurance market, generated insurance premiums last year of just over
Dollars 1bn. Its profits are not broken down separately, but Textron said it
made a 'substantial contribution' to earnings in 1992.
Textron said it would offer 7.5m shares in the insurer for sale, and that an
over-allotment provision in the sale could take its holding down to 81 per
cent. The proceeds will be used to reduce debt, the company said.
</TEXT>
