FT  17 AUG 93 / Observer: Over-clouded
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Remember Bill Hussey, the mining man who was sent to look for gold in
Kazakhstan and found his new mine was only a few mushroom clouds away from
the former Soviet Union's nuclear test sites? Observer was reassured to hear
that he has taken to carrying a geiger-counter. However, there was some
consternation recently when Hussey pointed his gadget towards the Broadgate
complex; it registered three times the level of radioactivity found in
Kazakhstan.
