FT  17 AUG 93 / Observer: Haggle time
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Hard to believe that with the stock market flirting with its all-time high
there are still some investment analysts who can't afford their subs.
However, the Institute of Investment Management and Research, which
represents Britain's 3,100 investment analysts, likes to think of itself as
a caring organisation. Hence, it has asked members not currently employed to
send a letter 'explaining their circumstances', and it will consider
deferring payment of its Pounds 81 a year subscription fee. The society
insists that this generous gesture is in no way related to the fact that it
has just raised membership fees by 8 per cent.
