<DATELINE>
   SEOUL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
CALM returned to South Korea's financial markets yesterday as the stock
market rebounded sharply after tumbling late last week in response to a ban
on the use of aliases in financial transactions, writes John Burton in
Seoul.
The general share price index rose by 25 points from Saturday's close to
691, although it still remains below the 725 level on Thursday when the ban
was announced.
Trading was brisk at 31m shares, twice last week's volume, as investors took
advantage of buying opportunities.
