<HEADLINE>
FT  17 AUG 93 / Factions reach deal on Sarajevo
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A PLAN to put Sarajevo under temporary United Nations control was agreed 'in
principle' last night by the leaders of Bosnia's three warring factions.
The city's fate would be put on ice during negotiations on a three-way
carve-up of the rest of Bosnia on ethnic lines.
Earlier Mr Alija Izetbegovic, Bosnia's Moslem president, had insisted that
ending the siege of Sarajevo must top the agenda of the latest talks on the
country's 17-month conflict.
The accord came just hours after Serb, Croat and Moslem leaders resumed
negotiations for the first time in two weeks.
However, officials warned that the agreement was not yet finalised. Mr John
Mills, spokesman for the international mediators, said: 'The devil is always
in the details.'
